 incubating under Redeemer Presbyterian (PCA). | Field: San Antonio, Texas | Comms: Substack ''''Kirby Family Update — June 2025'''' (June 2025)', 9, 'Actively raising personal planting funds from individual donors through a dedicated account opened by his sending church; runs a personal Substack newsletter with family and fundraising updates.', 'hunter:church-planters', 'pending', '{"h": "church-planters", "src": "https://colejkirby.substack.com/p/church-planting-update"}'::jsonb),('Jacob Giles (South Boston church plant (with Renewal Church))', 'individual', 'gilesboston.substack.com', 'Family relocating from the Southeast to plant in South Boston in partnership with Renewal Church; documents the journey in the ''''Giles Family Newsletter (Boston Church Plant)'''' Substack with numbered ''''From Boston'''' updates. | Field: South Boston, Massachusetts | Comms: Substack ''''From Boston 08: March Madness'''' (spring 2026)', 9, 'Traveling to churches and families to raise monthly financial partners for the plant, with a direct give link and personal contact for new monthly partners; very active newsletter in an expensive US c', 'hunter:church-planters', 'pending', '{"h": "church-planters", "src": "https://gilesboston.substack.com"}'::jsonb),('Nathan Sanders (Flower City Church)', 'individual', 'elimfellowship.org/article-detail/planting-a-new-church-in-2026', 'Nathan and Emily Sanders are planting Flower City Church under Elim Fellowship (with Stadia-network connections), targeting Rochester''''s diverse south city and university crowds; official launch Sunday, October 4, 2026. | Field: Rochester, New York (south city / univer | Comms: First newsletter prayer update via Elim Fellowship announcement (2026)', 9, 'Pre-launch plant explicitly asking for monthly supporters, one-time gifts, and strategic donations to cover operating costs; just released first newsletter/prayer update with signup — classic fundrais', 'hunter:church-planters', 'pending', '{"h": "church-planters", "src": "https://elimfellowship.org/article-detail/planting-a-new-church-in-2026"}'::jsonb),('Brandon Hawkes (Toccoa Church Plant (PCA))', 'individual', 'cpcclarkesville.org/ministries/toccoa-church-plant-2', 'Rev. Brandon Hawkes was called in spring 2024 to lead a new PCA church plant in Toccoa out of Christ Presbyterian Church Clarkesville; Georgia Foothills Presbytery approved the plant August 15, 2024. | Field: Toccoa, Georgia | Comms: Parent church website plant page and support-raising announcement (2025)', 9, 'Parent-church page states Brandon is raising support from individuals and churches to get the fledgling congregation started — a PCA planter squarely in the individual-donor fundraising phase.', 'hunter:church-planters', 'pending', '{"h": "church-planters", "src": "https://cpcclarkesville.org/ministries/toccoa-church-plant-2/"}'::jsonb),('Raph Peters (Southside Fellowship Church)', 'individual', 'southsidefellowship.church', 'Raph Peters co-planted Southside Fellowship (planted 2022 out of Sojourn Montrose) in Houston''''s Third Ward; church is part of Acts 29, the Sojourn Houston family, and the Crete Collective. | Field: Third Ward / OST-South Union, Houston, T | Comms: Union Baptist Association planter interview and active Reliant giving page (2025', 9, 'Maintains a personal missionary-style support page on Reliant (reliant.org/raph.peters), meaning he raises personal support from individual donors while pastoring a young plant; named planter with act', 'hunter:church-planters', 'pending', '{"h": "church-planters", "src": "https://reliant.org/raph.peters"}'::jsonb),('Jake Woodfin (Branches Church SF)', 'individual', 'woodfincrew.com', 'Jake and Hali Woodfin moved to San Francisco in 2019 as independent Baptist church-planting missionaries and launched Branches Church in the Sunset District (grand opening September 2021); woodfincrew.com is their personal planter site. | Field: Sunset District, San Francisco, Californ | Comms: YouTube ''''Woodfin